	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I used VS2010 for most of the development for Ghost in the Machine, then moved to VS2012 late 2013. The game also has been built for Linux and Mac OS X, and my C++ is 100% the same across platforms. Of course the build environment was different on each (g++ for linux until I switched to clang++, OS X using Xcode with clang). I'm sure you can find situations where your code will only work in VS, but I've noticed a lot of that comes from some slight laxness in implementation. By following standards, everything has worked without anything being VS / Windows specific.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
